To Our Readers:


ABCNEWS.com has the latest on what's making headlines in the United States

and in Afghanistan:


The Taliban is pledging to fight to defend the territory in Afghanistan

they still have, while the commander of the U.S. war effort said "we will

prevail" in clearing the Taliban out of Kunduz. Meanwhile, Osama bin Laden

reportedly ordered his top lieutenants to kill him to keep him from being

captured by U.S. troops.

http://abcnews.go.com/sections/world/DailyNews/STRIKE_MAIN.html


Officials have confirmed that an elderly rural Connecticut woman is

infected with inhalation anthrax in a case that has baffled authorities.

http://abcnews.go.com/sections/us/DailyNews/US_ANTHRAX.html


Plus,


ABCNEWS.com wishes a Happy Thanksgiving to you and your family. Get turkey

tips, recipes and fun family crafts.

